    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>A form of turret lathe usually having a hollow spindle through which a bar can be fed to be machined into bolts, studs, and other screws.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000042061/Webster's Third New International Dictionary (1961)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Een type revolverdraaibank, meestal met een holle as waar een staaf doorheen kan worden gevoerd om machinaal te worden verwerkt tot bouten, nagels en schroeven.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
